01400nai  2200301 i 4500001001400000003000800014005001700022006001900039007001500058008004100073020004800114040003500162050001000197082001400207245005400221264005200275300002200327336002100349337002300370338003200393310003200425520039400457588009300851650002500944650002600969700003400995856006901029EDZ0000055057StDuBDS20171101143006.0m||||||||d||||||||cr |||||||||||120124c20079999nyu|| d|o|||| 0   a|eng|d  a9781561592630 (online resource) :cNo price  aStDuBDSbengcStDuBDSerdaepn 4aML10004a780.322300aGrove music online /ceditor, Anna-Lise Santella. 1a[New York] :bOxford University Press,c[2007-]  a1 online resource  atext2rdacontent  acomputer2rdamedia  aonline resource2rdacarrier  aFrequency of update unknown8 a'Grove Music Online' is an authoritative resource for music with over 60,000 articles written by over 6000 scholars charting the diverse history, theory and cultures of music around the globe. Based on a work first published in 1879 and updated frequently, it has been in continuous publication for over a century and now published hundreds of new articles and article revisions each year.  aDescription based on online resource; title from home page (viewed on November 1, 2017). 0aMusicvDictionaries. 0aMusicvEncyclopedias.1 aSantella, Anna-Lise,eeditor.403Oxford music onlineuhttp://www.oxfordmusiconline.com/grovemusic01531nam  2200301 i 4500001001400000003000800014005001700022006001900039007001500058008004100073020003800114040003500152050002100187082001400208245005200222250002500274264004800299300002200347336002100369337002300390338003200413520049600445588009300941650002501034650002901059700004401088856009701132EDZ0000171564StDuBDS20171103133012.0m||||||||d||||||||cr |||||||||||131101s2011    enk     o|    000|0|eng|d  a9780199579037 (ebook) :cNo price  aStDuBDSbengcStDuBDSerdaepn 4aML100b.S37 201104a780.322304aThe Oxford companion to music /cAlison Latham.  aOnline-only edition. 1a[Oxford] :bOxford University Press,c2011.  a1 online resource  atext2rdacontent  acomputer2rdamedia  aonline resource2rdacarrier8 aThis online-only edition of The Oxford Companion to Music is a partial revision that focuses on living composers and their music, and adds some terms, works, and cross-references to the original text. Bibliographies have also been substantially revised and updated. This classic reference work includes articles that range from clear, concise definitions of musical ideas and terms to extended surveys of musical forms and styles, with specialist coverage of virtually every musical subject.  aDescription based on online resource; title from home page (viewed on November 1, 2013). 0aMusicvDictionaries. 0aMusicvBio-bibliography.1 aLatham, Alison,eeditor of compilation.40uhttp://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780199579037.001.0001/acref-978019957903701671nam  2200385 i EDZ0000126899StDuBDS20171103133013.0m||||||||d||||||||cr |||||||||||130423s2012    enka   fo|    000|0|eng|d  a9780191744518 (ebook) :cNo price  aStDuBDSbengcStDuBDSerdaepn 4aML10004a780.32231 aKennedy, Michael,d1926-2014,eauthor.10aConcise Oxford dictionary of music14aThe Oxford dictionary of music /cMichael Kennedy and Joyce Bourne Kennedy.30aDictionary of music  aSixth edition /bedited by Tim Rutherford-Johnson. 1aOxford :bOxford University Press,c2012.  a1 online resource (1 volume (unpaged)) :billustrations (black and white)  atext2rdacontent  astill image2rdacontent  acomputer2rdamedia  aonline resource2rdacarrier  aPrevious edition: published as The concise Oxford dictionary of music. 2007.8 a'The Oxford Dictionary of Music' is a guide for all music lovers and performers, both amateur and professional. It brings together 12,500 entries covering musical subjects of all kinds in an authoritative and accessible way.  aSpecialized.  aDescription based on print version record. 0aMusicvDictionaries.1 aKennedy, Joyce Bourne,eauthor.1 aRutherford-Johnson, Tim,eeditor.08iPrint version :z978019957810840uhttp://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780199578108.001.0001/acref-978019957810801310nam  2200289 a 4500001001400000003000800014005001700022006001900039007001500058008004100073020003800114040003000152050002400182082001700206245008800223250001200311260004600323300003000369500003900399504005100438520029900489588004700788650003400835700001900869776003500888856009700923EDZ0000171555StDuBDS20171103133014.0m||||||||d||||||||cr |||||||||||131023s2006    enk     o|    001|0|eng|d  a9780199726363 (ebook) :cNo price  aStDuBDSbengcStDuBDSepn 4aML102.P66bG84 200604a781.640322304aThe encyclopedia of popular musich[electronic resource] /cedited by Colin Larkin.  a4th ed.  aOxford :bOxford University Press,c2006.  a1 online resource (10 v.)  aPrevious ed.: London : Muze, 1998.  aIncludes bibliographical references and index.8 aColin Larkin provides information on a range of popular music genre from 1900s onwards; including rock, pop, jazz, folk blues, heavy metal, techno, R&B, reggae, and hip-hop. This biographical encyclopedia contains a name index, an index of song titles, and bibliographies by artist and subject.  aDescription based on print version record. 0aPopular musicvEncyclopedias.1 aLarkin, Colin.08iPrint version :z978019531373440uhttp://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780195313734.001.0001/acref-9780195313734